node.text:
In this video I show you guys the process of us getting our car ready to list on Hyrecar! My wife’s phone died in the middle of the video so we couldn’t finish lol but we still got a lot done.

I’ll be documenting the entire process here on Instagram. We are posting the car later today or early tomorrow to get It approved for rental.

#hyrecar #turo #rentalcar #rentalcars #carfleet #carrental #businesslifestyle #newbusinessventure #passiveincomestream #sidehustleideas

node.text:
Quick come up. Business isn’t complicated, people complicate business.

Find a skill, monetize that skill. That’s It.

In my training I show you how to get started in less than 30 days with $100 or less.

I show you where to get the parts, how to do the repairs, how to get customers, and I give you access to a private group with over 3000 members.

You’ll get everything you need from information and motivation. It’s up to you to take a leap, but either way we gonna eat!

Dm me “PR” and I’ll send you the link to the training.

Share this with someone looking for a side hustle, including yourself 😂

node.text:
9-5 Made me depressed. I’ll keep It 100. I used to think there was something wrong with me lol, like I needed therapy because I legit dreaded going into work.

As soon as I clocked in, I was ready to clock out. I don’t know how I lasted as long as I did. I was ready to adopt some kids or something so the government could give me checks or maybe join the national guard or the army because ANYTHING would have been better than office politics and annoying customers. 

On a serious not though, Mental health is important. I’ve spoken to plenty of people that felt the way I did including friends and family, but when I asked why they stayed, they told me they just dealt with It. I get It. You have kids and bills etc, me too. I just couldn’t do It. There were times I quit jobs and didn’t even have another one lined up because I was so sick of em. That’s why side hustling became a part of my life. 

I know people that are able to deal with the stress of a job and still function, bless you if that’s you cuz I couldn’t do It.

If you’re one of the people that feel lost like your head is gonna fall off if you stick in there another day, I feel you. Breathe fam, it’s gonna be ok. Step one, start dabbling in some side hustles.

Follow me @nycphonebuyer, watch some of my content, do what you gotta do but don’t keep procrastinating. It’s only a matter of time before you break down from job related stress and can’t take It no more.

If you need to, speak to a therapist, I did when I had a job. Therapy is underrated. But definitely get away from that toxic environment.

Free training via link in bio to start a phone repair business. Full training available once you check that out if you’re interested.

#mentalhealthawareness #jobstress #onthejob #mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealthrecovery #therapyworks

node.text:
Alright fam! It’s time!!!! We got our first rental request and are working things out with the renter. His request is for 3 days and we are going to do contactless pickup. This means he will be picking up the car and everything remotely.

My #1 goal this year was to start really developing passive income and this is just the start. I really dragged my feet with getting our rental car business started but we finally here! Much love and respect to everyone that’s been following the journey up to this point.

This car will generate $6-900 profit per month and we plan to keep getting more and more!

Follow me @nycphonebuyer for more side hustle income tips! I’ll be sharing our entire Hyrecar journey here on Instagram and answering any questions you guys have on saved live videos.

node.text:
You can’t wait on anyone else to go out there and be great, you’ve got to make It happen yourself. Don’t rely on friends, family, or your spouse to support your dreams.

Opportunity is everywhere, but most times, it won’t find you so you have to go out and find It. 

Yesterday I was speaking to one of my students about imposter syndrome. He told me sometimes he feels like things are going too good, so he’s just hoping they don’t go bad. My philosophy is to focus on the good and look for ways to make It better. I believe in the law of attraction.

The same way you notice the car you drive on the road more than any other car, you’ll notice the things in life you think about the most. Focus on negativity, and that’s all you’ll receive.

You’re in control of your life, your outcomes, and your journey. Don’t ever forget that.

I’ve put together a training to show you how to take even more control, so go cop that via link in bio! You can take the free training and even get the full training on sale for a limited time only. Labor Day Special.

Follow @nycphonebuyer

node.text:
Consistency.

Imagine making this in one day outside of your day job? First time I touched a rack outside my 9-5, I knew I had options. I started this business with no lending, all profits reinvested over the years.

I’ve learned there are better ways you can grow your business though and I’ve made the mistakes so you don’t have to. Did you know after you make $10k in sales a month for 3-5 months consecutively that PayPal might potentially extend you a loan offer?

You can use this money to build your already budding business.

For those of you starting from $0, you can use a credit card or apply for PayPal credit to get a couple hundred bucks to get the ball rolling.

For those of you with bad credit like I had when I got started, you can list old junk around the house on eBay. I sold an iPhone I was using and downgraded at one point to get some extra cash and invest $100 in my business.

You don’t need a ton of capital to start a side hustle, you just need a dolla and a dream. Follow @nycphonebuyer for more. Tap link in bio to grab the free training that teaches the 5 steps needed to get started in phone repair in under 30 days with $100 or less.

#sidehustler #phonerepair #ebayseller #swappa #ebayreseller #ebayresellercommunity #fixandflip #refurbished #refurbish #makemoney

node.text:
I just wanna be a good role model. 

My baby boy is 2 years old now and he literally copies everything I do. Last night he fell asleep on me and as I held him in my arms I was reminded of why I push as hard as I do. My oldest son is 13 and he starts tomorrow at a brand new school so he’s nervous.

Today we took him school shopping and It just made me realize how grateful I am to even be in a position to take him school shopping.

Being a young parent is no joke. My wife and I were not even 21 when we had our first kid. So I wanna let y’all know it’s possible, no matter your circumstances.

We had a kid at a young age and another kid when we were older. Yes it’s tough building a business while you have kids, but you know what’s tougher? Being away from them to go to work.

Stay strong. Stay consistent. Stay blessed.

node.text:
Shipped out 15 packages today, $3000 in revenue 25% margin net, and about 4 hours of work. 

Get you a side hustle ASAP!

It might just turn into a main gig. 

We buy broken phones from auctions on eBay, and we also have a buyback site we use to source. The hustle is buying them broken, fixing them, and flipping them. 

The learning curve for most people is about 2-4 hours to complete the first repair and about a week or two to get good enough to start taking clients. This doesn’t take years to learn. Once you have a skill, you can use It to make money.

If you checkout the link in my bio, I’ve put together a lot of solid information for you to look at and learn more about the Billion dollar repair industry. People break their phones everyday, it’s time for you to learn how to fix em.

Follow @nycphonebuyer for more 

#makemoneyfromyourphone #getpaidnow #getpaidtotravel #workingman #workingwoman #blackmentalhealth #blackowned #blackwealthrenaissance

This used to be me everytime a customer hit me up for a repair. No cap 😂. 

It would be like 9pm at night and I’d be speeding on the cross Bronx expressway heading to a coffee shop or something to do a repair after work. 

You gotta do what you gotta do in order to get where you want to go. Reap what you sow.

Hard work doesn’t always result in an easy life, but It certainly increases your chances of getting there.

I’ve repaired thousands of cell phones, and taught thousands of people how to start a phone repair business. I’ve built a network of solid technicians I communicate with daily and we all dominate our areas. I have mobile guys outperforming repair shops in some areas.

The demand for this business is so high, It’s like Uber. More people need a driver than there are drivers available.

More people need a repair than there are technicians to repair them. 

If you’ve ever considered starting a side hustle, or teaching your kids about business then this is a great place to start. Phone repair is a family friendly skill that can be turned into a business. My phone repair business has allowed us to work from home and raise our kids without the stress of a job.

I’ve put together a training to show you how! Hit link in bio.

node.text:
No amount of money can make you love what you hate.

All they can do is pay you enough to fake.

I used to imagine a job that I’d be happy with if I made a certain amount of money. In 2018 I got a promotion that put me in a position financially to rise up and make the money I needed to make so I could be financially stress free. I was happy for a while, maybe like 2 weeks, then I became even more miserable than before.

My life was dependent upon rather or not I kept the job I had at the time, and my understanding about jobs is that companies do go out of business and when they do you go with them. That always scared me. I always stayed up late at night afraid of what would happen if I bought a nice house and a car depending on the income from a job and then all of a sudden I get fired? I never understood how that sat well with people. 

Maybe Im being extra, but It was a genuine concern, especially when the bank started letting managers go because they launched EATMs that let customers do things on their own with higher limits. Getting replaced by technology and being made obsolete was one of my biggest fears, in addition to not liking to annoying customers that came in day to day to argue about overdraft fees. I was over It. 

I started a business to get away from all the concerns and stressors of a job, and that came with It’s own set of problems, but these are problems I embraced because It meant no one could fire me. 

When you own a business you’re taking a risk. When you have a job you’re taking a risk. My advice? Do both until you can survive with just one.

node.text:
A lot of people have trouble understanding this. You gotta be happy for the homies, otherwise you gonna lose em.

I never look at my friends or associates with envy because the people around me either got a hand up or we moving together. When you see someone winning, don’t try to poke holes in the circle, instead, get in.

It’s not very hard to be a winner, but it’s really easy to be a loser.

If you want to win, all you have to do is learn how to be happy for yourself and others when they have things you desire. It’s ok to want what other people have, but it’s not ok to hate them for It.

Focus on your purpose and your pace, that’s how you’ll find your peace.

It don’t matter what the next man doing, what matters is what you’re NOT doing.

I’m here to be the hand up, in case nobody in your life willing to do that for you, what I expect in return is for you to hustle and grind like your life depend on It.

I drop the gems I drop because I was taught that sharing is caring, and I got nothing but love for y’all.

Stay strong 💪🏿
